Text.SourceString: Whoa! A new friend! Who are you?
Text.LocalizedString: Whoa! A new friend! Who are you?

Text.SourceString: You look really different from me... You're definitely not a panda, are you?
Text.LocalizedString: You look really different from me... You're definitely not a panda, are you?

Text.SourceString: Hey there, friends! You're back!
Text.LocalizedString: Hey there, friends! You're back!

Text.SourceString: Welcome back, friend! I tried counting the leaves in the forest while waiting for you – let’s just say, it’s a lot!
Text.LocalizedString: Welcome back, friend! I tried counting the leaves in the forest while waiting for you – let’s just say, it’s a lot!

Text.SourceString: Hiya, pals! How are you?
Text.LocalizedString: Hiya, pals! How are you?

Text.SourceString: Yoohoo, <PlayerName>$Player</>! It's you!
Text.LocalizedString: Yoohoo, <PlayerName>$Player</>! It's you!

Text.SourceString: Bet you can't guess what I found today – a leaf shaped like a heart! Nature’s full of surprises, isn't it?
Text.LocalizedString: Bet you can't guess what I found today – a leaf shaped like a heart! Nature’s full of surprises, isn't it?

Text.SourceString: I was playing my flute by the creek the other today, and you won't believe it – the frogs started croaking along!//We ended up having a jam session right there by the water.
Text.LocalizedString: I was playing my flute by the creek the other today, and you won't believe it – the frogs started croaking along!//We ended up having a jam session right there by the water.

Text.SourceString: I was about to ask the river for a new flute tune. Want to help me listen for it?
Text.LocalizedString: I was about to ask the river for a new flute tune. Want to help me listen for it?

Text.SourceString: Do you think the stars ever get tired of twinkling all night?//Sometimes, when I play my flute to the moon, I like to imagine they're dancing to my melody.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you think the stars ever get tired of twinkling all night?//Sometimes, when I play my flute to the moon, I like to imagine they're dancing to my melody.

Text.SourceString: I found this really twisty, turny bamboo shoot today.//It reminded me of you – always full of surprises!
Text.LocalizedString: I found this really twisty, turny bamboo shoot today.//It reminded me of you – always full of surprises!

Text.SourceString: Guess what? There's someone who plays the flute around here! Never seen them, but wow, their tunes are super cool.//It's not you, is it?
Text.LocalizedString: Guess what? There's someone who plays the flute around here! Never seen them, but wow, their tunes are super cool.//It's not you, is it?

Text.SourceString: Sometimes, I wonder if it's just me playing tricks on myself. I mean, I am the master of the flute around here. Maybe I'm sleep-fluting? Is that a thing?
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes, I wonder if it's just me playing tricks on myself. I mean, I am the master of the flute around here. Maybe I'm sleep-fluting? Is that a thing?

Text.SourceString: Have you heard the mysterious flute music in the forest? Some of those melodies are really catchy – I can't help but hum along!
Text.LocalizedString: Have you heard the mysterious flute music in the forest? Some of those melodies are really catchy – I can't help but hum along!

Text.SourceString: I'm starting to think maybe it's a ghost! This part of the forest could totally be haunted, right? Spooky but cool – a ghost with a flute.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm starting to think maybe it's a ghost! This part of the forest could totally be haunted, right? Spooky but cool – a ghost with a flute.

Text.SourceString: Get this – I heard someone talking to a tree the other day, saying 'You're doing great today, tree.' That's kind of funny, isn't it?
Text.LocalizedString: Get this – I heard someone talking to a tree the other day, saying 'You're doing great today, tree.' That's kind of funny, isn't it?

Text.SourceString: When it rains, my whole house feels like a fresh, clean, green painting. And the smell? Just wow!
Text.LocalizedString: When it rains, my whole house feels like a fresh, clean, green painting. And the smell? Just wow!

Text.SourceString: Rainy days in my bamboo home are like nature's invitation to play some tunes. How about we practice together?
Text.LocalizedString: Rainy days in my bamboo home are like nature's invitation to play some tunes. How about we practice together?

Text.SourceString: Sometimes, I try to match my flute tunes with the thunder.//It calms me down a bit.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes, I try to match my flute tunes with the thunder.//It calms me down a bit.

Text.SourceString: Storms make me a teeny bit nervous. Can I hang out at your place until it calms down?//But wait, who'll keep an eye on my house then?
Text.LocalizedString: Storms make me a teeny bit nervous. Can I hang out at your place until it calms down?//But wait, who'll keep an eye on my house then?

Text.SourceString: I love how snowflakes fall so softly. It's like nature's way of saying 'shh, let's have a quiet day'.
Text.LocalizedString: I love how snowflakes fall so softly. It's like nature's way of saying 'shh, let's have a quiet day'.

Text.SourceString: Everything's so quiet when it snows.
Text.LocalizedString: Everything's so quiet when it snows.

Text.SourceString: Snowball fights?
Text.LocalizedString: Snowball fights?

Text.SourceString: On cozy days like this, it's all about long naps for me.
Text.LocalizedString: On cozy days like this, it's all about long naps for me.

Text.SourceString: Hey, why do I always get extra hungry so fast during Winter? Do you get hungrier too when it's cold?
Text.LocalizedString: Hey, why do I always get extra hungry so fast during Winter? Do you get hungrier too when it's cold?

Text.SourceString: Have you ever just laid back and watched the clouds? They have the coolest shapes!
Text.LocalizedString: Have you ever just laid back and watched the clouds? They have the coolest shapes!

Text.SourceString: The hot spring here is super awesome! But oh boy, does it get crowded.//I like going there when it's just me.
Text.LocalizedString: The hot spring here is super awesome! But oh boy, does it get crowded.//I like going there when it's just me.

Text.SourceString: Sleeping in is the best! You wake up, and the sun is there. Bam!
Text.LocalizedString: Sleeping in is the best! You wake up, and the sun is there. Bam!

Text.SourceString: I need a nap...
Text.LocalizedString: I need a nap...

Text.SourceString: Tripped over a bamboo root again! Those sneaky things always catch me off guard.
Text.LocalizedString: Tripped over a bamboo root again! Those sneaky things always catch me off guard.

Text.SourceString: Sat on a prickly bush yesterday– talk about an unexpected poke in the rear!
Text.LocalizedString: Sat on a prickly bush yesterday– talk about an unexpected poke in the rear!

Text.SourceString: Climbing a tree seemed fun until I realized falling isn't. Good thing the ground was there to catch me.
Text.LocalizedString: Climbing a tree seemed fun until I realized falling isn't. Good thing the ground was there to catch me.

Text.SourceString: Ever get your head stuck in a bamboo cluster? I don't recommend it.
Text.LocalizedString: Ever get your head stuck in a bamboo cluster? I don't recommend it.

Text.SourceString: I once mistook a sleeping skunk for a rock. Let's just say, I learned a new scent that day.
Text.LocalizedString: I once mistook a sleeping skunk for a rock. Let's just say, I learned a new scent that day.

Text.SourceString: Trying to juggle bamboo sticks seemed like a fun idea until one landed right on my toe. Bamboo is tougher than it looks!
Text.LocalizedString: Trying to juggle bamboo sticks seemed like a fun idea until one landed right on my toe. Bamboo is tougher than it looks!

Text.SourceString: Oh boy, I went to that house on the hill and climbed a big dome there! Ended up in a vine-tangle mess.//But it so much fun!
Text.LocalizedString: Oh boy, I went to that house on the hill and climbed a big dome there! Ended up in a vine-tangle mess.//But it so much fun!

Text.SourceString: We should totally do it together next time. I can spot you, and you can spot me.
Text.LocalizedString: We should totally do it together next time. I can spot you, and you can spot me.

Text.SourceString: The frogs here! They're my favorite.//Hey, where are you hiding, little froggies? Come out, come out, wherever you are!
Text.LocalizedString: The frogs here! They're my favorite.//Hey, where are you hiding, little froggies? Come out, come out, wherever you are!

Text.SourceString: I learned a new flute tune today! It sounds like raindrops dancing on a bamboo roof. Want to hear it?
Text.LocalizedString: I learned a new flute tune today! It sounds like raindrops dancing on a bamboo roof. Want to hear it?

Text.SourceString: A bird whistled back when I played my flute. Do you think it was trying to teach me a new song?
Text.LocalizedString: A bird whistled back when I played my flute. Do you think it was trying to teach me a new song?

Text.SourceString: I played my flute so loudly today that a squirrel started dancing! Or maybe it was just looking for nuts...I couldn't really tell.
Text.LocalizedString: I played my flute so loudly today that a squirrel started dancing! Or maybe it was just looking for nuts...I couldn't really tell.

Text.SourceString: I found the crunchiest bamboo shoot today!
Text.LocalizedString: I found the crunchiest bamboo shoot today!

Text.SourceString: I raced a rabbit today! It was super fast, but I think I almost won.
Text.LocalizedString: I raced a rabbit today! It was super fast, but I think I almost won.

Text.SourceString: I'm thinking of opening a bamboo snack bar. First recipe: bamboo with a hint of honey!//So, how many talking pandas do you think live around here?
Text.LocalizedString: I'm thinking of opening a bamboo snack bar. First recipe: bamboo with a hint of honey!//So, how many talking pandas do you think live around here?

Text.SourceString: A butterfly landed on my nose today. It tickled!
Text.LocalizedString: A butterfly landed on my nose today. It tickled!

Text.SourceString: I tried to chat with an owl last night. It just blinked at me. Hmm...
Text.LocalizedString: I tried to chat with an owl last night. It just blinked at me. Hmm...

Text.SourceString: I watched the stars last night and tried to connect them like a dot-to-dot. I made a bamboo shape!
Text.LocalizedString: I watched the stars last night and tried to connect them like a dot-to-dot. I made a bamboo shape!

Text.SourceString: Do you think the moon ever gets lonely up there? Maybe that's why it comes to visit every night.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you think the moon ever gets lonely up there? Maybe that's why it comes to visit every night.

Text.SourceString: What if we could talk to the rain? I'd ask it to fall only on the plants, not on my head!
Text.LocalizedString: What if we could talk to the rain? I'd ask it to fall only on the plants, not on my head!

Text.SourceString: I helped a tiny bug find its way back to the grass. It's nice to be helpful.//So, what about you? What did you do today?
Text.LocalizedString: I helped a tiny bug find its way back to the grass. It's nice to be helpful.//So, what about you? What did you do today?
